    statisticsNote: 'Conventional INSERT loads all blocks through the buffer cache. The APPEND hint forces direct path load, bypassing the cache entirely — reducing dirty buffer accumulation for bulk INSERT workloads.',
    fixSummary: '(1) Add /*+ APPEND */ to the INSERT to use direct path load. (2) Increase db_writer_processes. (3) Partition the target table to distribute writes. (4) Review concurrent INSERT session count — reduce concurrency if above DBWR write capacity.',
